<problem display_name="Solve for A, again" linenum="372" tex_filename="./block2/morematrixops.tex" showanswer="finished" attempts="1" rerandomize="per_student">
  <text>
    <p>
Suppose that [mathjaxinline]A,B,C,D[/mathjaxinline] are all invertible [mathjaxinline]n\times n[/mathjaxinline] matrices such that [mathjaxinline]B^ t (A^{-1})^ t = D^ t C^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]. Solve for [mathjaxinline]A[/mathjaxinline]. </p>
    <p>
      <multiplechoiceresponse>
        <choicegroup direction="vertical">
          <choice correct="false" name="1">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=D^{-1}C^ t B[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="2">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=B^{-1}D^{-1}C^ t[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="true" name="3">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=BD^{-1}C^ t[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="4">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=D^{-1}(C^{-1})^ t B[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="5">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=DC^ t B^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="6">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=C^ t D^{-1}B^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="7">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=BC^ t D^{-1}[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="8">
            <text> [mathjaxinline]A=C^ t D^{-1}B[/mathjaxinline]</text>
          </choice>
          <choice correct="false" name="9">
            <text> None of the above</text>
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </p>
    <p>
      <solution>
        <font color="blue">Answer: </font>
        <font color="blue">
          <p>
 One possible procedure: left-multiply on both sides of the equation by [mathjaxinline](B^ t)^{-1}[/mathjaxinline] to obtain </p>
          <table id="a0000000133" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax](A^{-1})^ t = (B^ t)^{-1}D^ t C^{-1}.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 Take the transpose of both sides: </p>
          <table id="a0000000134" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]A^{-1}= ((B^ t)^{-1}D^ t C^{-1})^ t = (C^{-1})^ t D ((B^ t)^{-1})^ t = (C^ t)^{-1}D B^{-1}.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
          <p>
 Now we can take the inverse of both sides, and we get </p>
          <table id="a0000000135" class="equation" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="7" style="table-layout:auto">
            <tr>
              <td class="equation" style="width:80%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;border-style:hidden">[mathjax]A = B D^{-1}C^ t.[/mathjax]</td>
              <td class="eqnnum" style="width:20%;vertical-align:middle;text-align:left;border-style:hidden"/>
            </tr>
          </table>
        </font>
      </solution>
    </p>
  </text>
</problem>
